# Header action hierarchy

Each header row (app shell, `.z-mail-text-nav__row`, settings nav bar) may have **at most one primary action**.

## Primary action (local header, trailing edge)

The main outcome lives in a **`.z-header-action-zone`** at the trailing edge of the **pane header** that owns the action — not the far app-shell corner on wide desktop.

| Requirement | Detail |
|-------------|--------|
| **Class** | `.z-mail-text-nav__action` inside `.z-header-action-zone` |
| **Element** | `<a>` for navigation, `<button>` for in-place actions (Send, Reply) |
| **Look** | Semibold accent text, no button chrome, no icon — label only |
| **Hover** | Accent underline |
| **Zone** | Left border + padding isolates the action from filters / secondary links |

The primary action is **always the trailing (rightmost) element** of its header row, after every secondary link and overflow trigger, so it stands out.

Examples:
- **Inbox list (desktop)**: filters left (All · Unseen · Important) · **New message** in list-pane header zone
- **Inbox (mobile shell)**: **New** link in app shell end
- **Reader**: secondary links · More · **Reply** / **Send** zone (trailing)
- **Compose**: Discard / Rich text / Attach · **Send** zone (trailing)
- **Search (no list toolbar)**: **New message** stays in app shell end

Do **not** use `Button`, filled pills, or icon+label buttons for the primary header action.

## Secondary actions

| Role | Class / pattern | Weight |
|------|-----------------|--------|
| Secondary links | `.z-mail-text-nav__link` | normal |
| Destructive secondary | `.z-mail-text-nav__link--danger` | normal |
| Overflow / More / Actions | `textTrigger` + `.z-mail-text-nav__link` | normal |
| Utility icons (search, etc.) | `IconButton` | — |
| Title / folder name | `.z-mail-text-nav__title` | normal — never bold |
| Brand / logo | plain text in shell — **not** `.z-type-brand` | normal |

## Layout pattern

```
[ secondary links / filters … ]  |  [ primary __action in .z-header-action-zone ]
```

On mobile shell only, inbox **New** may sit in `.z-app-shell-header__end` when the list toolbar is in the shell center.

Bulk select bar (one row, never wraps): `[✓ master][▾ select]` · `N selected` (flex-1) · mark links (`Unsee` / `Mark seen` / `Important` / `Not important`, collapsed into a **More** overflow menu when more than two apply) · `Cancel` · separated **Trash** primary in `.z-header-action-zone` (`.z-mail-text-nav__action--danger`, trailing/standout). Text links like reader/compose, not icon buttons.

## Do not

- Put `font-semibold` / `font-bold` on titles, logos, or summary text in headers
- Use `.z-type-brand` in app shell or text-nav titles (reserve for auth/marketing pages)
- Style overflow triggers with `.z-mail-text-nav__action`
- Add a second primary action (e.g. Trash + Send both as `__action`)
- Use `Button` variant primary/ghost for the header’s main CTA

## When adding a header

1. Pick the single primary outcome → `.z-mail-text-nav__action` inside `.z-header-action-zone` on the owning pane header
2. Demote everything else → `__link`, `IconButton`, or overflow menu
3. Keep the title/logo at normal weight
4. On wide desktop, avoid placing mail actions in `.z-app-shell-header__end` when the list/reader/compose pane already has a header row
